ðŸ“˜ Java Records â€“ OCP Summary
Concept	            Details
record	            Defines a final immutable class with auto-generated code
Accessors	        Named exactly as the fields (no getX())
Constructor	        Canonical or compact constructors allowed
Inheritance	        Cannot extend any class (records are final)
Interfaces	        Can implement interfaces
Serialization	    Records are Serializable by default if fields are
Nested record	    Always static
Equality	        Shallow field-based equals() and hashCode()